  "text": "The LLVM optimization pipeline lifecycle flows as follows: (1) **PassBuilder** (defined in `llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilder.cpp`, line 507) is the entry point that constructs pipeline configurations and parses pass names. (2) **PassManager<IRUnitT>** (template class at `llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h`, line 162) is the core execution engine that iterates over registered passes and calls their `run()` methods. (3) **PassBuilderPipelines.cpp** assembles the default pipelines \u2014 `buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline` (line 1716) calls `buildModuleSimplificationPipeline` (line 1091) which calls `buildFunctionSimplificationPipeline` (line 592), constructing the O2 pipeline hierarchy. (4) **PassRegistry.def** is the registry file where all standard passes are declared via macros like `MODULE_PASS` (line 51+) and `FUNCTION_PASS` (line 433 for DSE: `FUNCTION_PASS(\"dse\", DSEPass())`). (5) **DeadStoreElimination.cpp** provides a concrete pass example: `DSEPass::run` (line 2746) invokes `eliminateDeadStores` (line 2710) to perform the actual optimization. The dependency chain is: PassBuilder reads PassRegistry.def to register passes \u2192 PassBuilderPipelines assembles them into the O2 pipeline \u2192 PassManager executes each pass by calling its `run()` method \u2192 DSEPass::run delegates to eliminateDeadStores.",
